data.enText: to make it difficult for sb to do sth or sth to happen

data.chText: 妨碍经济发展的政治局面
data.enText: a political situation that hinders economic growth

data.chText: 有些教师因资源不足而感到困难重重。
data.enText: Some teachers felt hindered by a lack of resources.

data.chText: 受伤后他无法发挥出最高水平。
data.enText: An injury was hindering him from playing his best.

example: The brace I have to wear is hindering my movements

tr: be a hindrance or obstacle to
example: She is impeding the progress of our project

tr: hinder or prevent the progress or accomplishment of
example: His brother blocked him at every turn

value.def: If something hinders you, it makes it more difficult for you to do something or make progress.

example.ex: Does the fact that your players are part-timers help or hinder you?...
example.tran: 队员们都是兼职的，这对你有利还是不利？

example.ex: Further investigation was hindered by the loss of all documentation on the case.
example.tran: 由于案件卷宗全部丢失致使进一步的调查受阻。

value.def: If something hinders your movement, it makes it difficult for you to move forward or move around.

example.ex: A thigh injury increasingly hindered her mobility...
example.tran: 大腿受伤使她行动愈发不便。

example.ex: Landslides and bad weather are continuing to hinder the arrival of relief supplies to the area.
example.tran: 滑坡和恶劣天气仍在阻碍救援物资运送到该地区。
